An 8-year-old boy was killed in a pre-dawn fire early Monday while his brother, 9, made a daring escape from their burning home by jumping from the second-story bedroom window.

According to police, Jayden Isme was killed at the scene of the townhouse fire, which was so intense firefighters were forced to retreat from the blaze.

His brother Justin Isme ran to a neighbor's house to call 911 after escaping and though he suffered minor injuries will survive.

