Neighbor Michael Florent, 31, described the brothers as friendly boys 'heavy into sports.'

'Always together,' he said. 'When you seen one, you seen the other one, always together.'

Justin attempted 'to get the other brother out but was unable to,' Butkus said.

The surviving brother was treated at the Plantation General Hospital.

The cause of the fire remains a mystery.

'There's nothing that I'm seeing or hearing that would indicate there
 was any type of real malicious activity that has gone on,' Butkus said. 'It appears to have been an unfortunate tragedy.'

